        {
            "id": "de32bb46ba4046df87186",
            "questionText": "An automated guided vehicle (AGV) starts from rest and accelerates at a rate of $!$0.5 \\frac{m}{s^2}$!$ for $!$5$!$ seconds. It then maintains a constant speed for $!$10$!$ seconds before decelerating at a rate of $!$1 \\frac{m}{s^2}$!$ until it comes to a stop. Calculate the total distance covered by the AGV during its journey.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "11867934b760487aa3afa",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by considering the acceleration phase. The AGV starts from rest and accelerates uniformly. Which formula correctly relates initial velocity, acceleration, and time to compute the final velocity?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "0e8a6662-eb83-48e0-a158-6f8a1acf9f25",
                        "976c240a-1fbe-4cc3-bec4-a1cd6c0c9f6a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = u + at$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = at$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$v = \\frac{s}{t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "c2eadeb830604a8193652",
                    "stepText": "Great. Now based on that, calculate the distance covered during the acceleration phase using the appropriate displacement equation for objects starting from rest. What is the distance covered in this phase?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "6.25"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "m",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "976c240a-1fbe-4cc3-bec4-a1cd6c0c9f6a"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$s = ut + \\frac{1}{2}at^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$s = vt$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$s = u + at^2$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "4780b6dbb7e3498e92ed8",
                    "stepText": "Now, consider the phase when the AGV is moving at a constant speed. Which simple relationship correctly gives the distance traveled during constant speed motion?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "e36724ff-c9a8-42ac-9b06-e20dc0863e14"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$s = vt$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$s = v + t$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$s = \\frac{v}{t}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "07a80582da944ffc98aa5",
                    "stepText": "Let's move on to the deceleration phase. The AGV slows down uniformly from its constant speed to a stop. Which formula would you use to calculate the stopping distance during deceleration?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "3.125"
